@node 6 " Chapter 6. Transmit advert."
It's too much for me to interpret, so I will just explain the most
important. I will now, explain some of the buttons at the bottom
of the screen.

TV-channel: TV2: Sends the Teletextpage first, and then the advert.
	    TV3: Just sends the advert.

wasted: Not so important

Pauseconfig: No.2 is the only one which is working. When there are
	     two similar sounds, an error often occurs. Therefore
	     its smart to have an extra break between these sounds.
@endnode


@node 7 " Chapter 7. Configuration file."
The file itself should be self-explaining, and can
be edited in a text-editor.

If you can't make it work, please check the following:

1. Check line 131 and 132 in your locale-file. The name and position
   of your config-file should be written here.

2. Line 133 in locale: The "on" declaration, written in capital
   letters.
   Line 134 in locale: The "off" declaration, written in capital
   letters.

3. The file must be at least 50 lines long. (very important)

4. The first variable at line 2, second at 5, third at 8 and
   so on.
@endnode


@node 8 " Chapter 8. Soundkeymapediting."
This is perhaps the most important file. And it shouldn't be
too hard to understand. It looks like this and should be
in S: or in the current directory:

"
  0123456789*#
 +------------
0|          0 
1|ABCDEFGHIJ1 
2|KLMNOPQRST2 
3|UVXYZĹĆŘ W3 
4|.,?!"-&+: 4 
5|          5 
6|          6 
7|          7 
8|          8 
9|          9 
*|            
#|            

Space: 56

Delete: *9
"

The file must be at least 19 lines long.
@endnode


@node 9 " Chapter 9. StttttS locale."
StttttS now supports Locale. Well, its not real locale, like in
wb3.0. But clean ascII files you can edit in a text editor.

To do:

1. Load "StttttSLocale.english" into a text-editor.

2. Interpret to another language.

3. Save the file as "StttttSLocale.<language>". It must be present in
   the current, or in the S: directory.

4. Write in cli: StttttS2.7 <sprĺk>.


If you translate into a new language, I would be very happy if you sent
me the file. If you do, you will always be placed in the credit-list, 
in the future, and you will recieve the last version of StttttS
registered version. And if you translate the configfile and the
keymap file, you will recieve a cable too.
@endnode


@node 10 " Chapter 10. How to register."
There are two versions of this program:

1. The registered version:

   1. The Programs StttttS V2.7, StttttS V2.7 demo version,
      The games Kjetlis I og Kjetlis II, the databases
      Fastbase 1.2 preview og List 1.3.
   2. 1 cable from your Amiga to your telephone.
   3. Information about updates. Future diskupdates will
      just cost postage+disk. Look @{"chapter 11" link 11}.

   This will just cost 100 @{"NOK" link NOK} for normal use and 300 NOK for
   commercial use. Posting will cost you about 10 NOK.

2. The @{"demo version" link dv}. This one is PD, and can be distributed freely.

To register:
1. Write your name and address.
2. write if it is for private or commercial use.
3. Send 100+10 or 300+10 NOK.

Norwegian Post giro: 0826 0813839, Kjetil S Matheussen, 3864 Rauland.
@endnode


